            "short_description": "Deploy IBM DevOps Loop — a unified Plan-Code-Build-Test-Release-Deploy-Measure platform — on IBM Cloud Kubernetes Service using Terraform and Helm.",
            "long_description": "This deployable architecture provisions a production-ready IBM DevOps Loop environment on IBM Cloud Kubernetes Service (IKS). It automates every step of the installation: VPC and cluster provisioning (optional), Emissary-ingress (Ambassador) API gateway setup, custom domain registration, TLS secret management via IBM Secrets Manager, HCL Harbor registry authentication, and the full DevOps Loop Helm chart deployment. Individual capabilities — Plan, Code, Control, Build, Test, Release, Deploy, and Measure — can be selectively enabled or disabled. The architecture also supports integration with IBM watsonx for the Loop Genie AI assistant.",
            "offering_docs_url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR_ORG/devops-loop-iks-da/main/README.md",
            "offering_icon_url": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
            "module_info": {},
            "support_details": "Community supported. Refer to IBM DevOps Loop documentation for product-level support at https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/devops-loop.",
